[[!meta description="How to enable three-finger and four-finger gestures with the Dell XPS 13 using Arch Linux and Touchègg"]]
[[!meta language="en"]]
[[!tag lang:en Arch Linux Dell-XPS-13]]

  1. Install the [linux-xps13-archlinux kernel](https://github.com/gunzy83/linux-xps13-archlinux) 
  (soon [in the AUR](https://aur.archlinux.org/packages.php?O=0&K=linux-xps13&do_Search=Go))

  2. Install `xf86-input-synaptics` and, from AUR, `touchegg` and
  `touchegg-gce-git` (this last one is to be able to configure
  gestures with the graphic interface).

  3. Edit `/etc/X11/xorg.conf.d/50-synaptics.conf`

        Section "InputClass"
            Identifier "touchpad catchall"
            Driver "synaptics"
            MatchIsTouchpad "on"
            Option "TapButton1" "1"
            Option "TapButton2" "2"
            Option "TapButton3" "0"
            Option "ClickFinger3" "0"

  4. Configure your gestures with Touchègg

    Here's my `~/.config/touchegg/touchegg.conf`:

    <script src="https://gist.github.com/hugoroy/10009770.js"></script>

  5. Add to your session (using `gnome-session-properties` for
  instance):
     - `touchegg`
     - `synclient TapButton3=0`
